There's a pronounced linguistic divide within the region. In 2010, English was the primary household language for 73.1% of residents in [Palm Beach County](/Palm_Beach_County) and 63.4% in [Broward County](/Broward_County). However, in [Miami-Dade County](/Miami-Dade_County), English was spoken at home by only 28.1% of residents, while Spanish was the dominant language for 63.8%.

