### Transportation

The Miami metropolitan area is a major transportation hub, with extensive infrastructure for road, air, and sea travel.

#### Roads

The region is served by five [interstate highways](/Interstate_Highway_System) managed by the [Florida Department of Transportation](/Florida_Department_of_Transportation) in conjunction with local authorities. [I-95](/Interstate_95_in_Florida) traverses the area north to south along the coast, terminating just south of [Downtown Miami](/Greater_Downtown_Miami) at [South Dixie Highway](/U.S._Route_1_in_Florida) ([US 1](/U.S._Route_1_in_Florida)). [I-75](/Interstate_75_in_Florida) runs east to west, curving south in western Broward County and linking suburban north Miami-Dade to [Naples](/Naples,_Florida) on the [Southwest Coast](/Southwest_Florida) via [Alligator Alley](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alligator_Alley), a route that cuts through the Florida [Everglades](/Everglades) before heading north. [I-595](/Interstate_595_(Florida)), also known as the Port Everglades Expressway, connects the Broward coast and Downtown [Fort Lauderdale](/Fort_Lauderdale,_Florida) to I-75 and Alligator Alley. In Miami, [I-195](/Interstate_195_(Florida)), the Airport Expressway, and [I-395](/Dolphin_East-West_Expressway), the Dolphin Expressway, divert traffic from the main I-95 route eastward toward [Biscayne Boulevard](/U.S._Route_1_in_Florida) (US 1) and [Miami Beach](/Miami_Beach), crossing [Biscayne Bay](/Biscayne_Bay) via the [Julia Tuttle](/Julia_Tuttle_Causeway) and [MacArthur](/MacArthur_Causeway) causeways. [Gratigny Parkway](/Florida_State_Road_924) connects northern Miami suburbs to the southern terminus of I-75. The [Palmetto Expressway](/Florida_State_Road_826), a crucial [beltway road](/Ring_road) for urban Miami, links I-95 and [Florida's Turnpike](/Florida%27s_Turnpike) at the [Golden Glades Interchange](/Golden_Glades_Interchange) near northeastern [North Miami Beach](/North_Miami_Beach,_Florida) to the southern inland suburbs of [Kendall](/Kendall,_Florida) and [Pinecrest](/Pinecrest,_Florida). The [Don Shula Expressway](/Florida_State_Road_874) and the [Homestead Extension of Florida's Turnpike](/Homestead_Extension_of_Florida%27s_Turnpike) form the southernmost section of the beltway, connecting the Palmetto Expressway to the [bedroom communities](/Commuter_town) of [Homestead](/Homestead,_Florida) and [Florida City](/Florida_City,_Florida). The [Snapper Creek Expressway](/Florida_State_Road_878) provides a connection from the Don Shula Expressway to South Dixie Highway (US 1).

In Greater Fort Lauderdale, the [Sawgrass Expressway (SR 869)](/Florida_State_Road_869) serves as the primary urban [bypass](/Bypass_(road)) route, linking the northern Broward County coast at I-95 and [Deerfield Beach](/Deerfield_Beach,_Florida) to I-595 and I-75 near [Sunrise](/Sunrise,_Florida).

Express lanes have been implemented on I-95, extending from [Miami-Dade County](/Miami-Dade_County,_Florida) into [Broward County](/Broward_County,_Florida). With increasing traffic congestion in South Florida, express lane projects have also been initiated in southern [Palm Beach County](/Palm_Beach_County,_Florida).

