#### College Sports

The most prominent collegiate sports program in the Miami metropolitan area belongs to the [Miami Hurricanes](/Miami_Hurricanes), representing the [University of Miami](/University_of_Miami) in [Coral Gables](/Coral_Gables,_Florida). They compete in [Division I](/NCAA_Division_I) of the [National Collegiate Athletic Association](/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association), the highest level of collegiate athletics. The University of Miami's [football team](/Miami_Hurricanes_football) has secured five national championships since 1983, and its [baseball team](/Miami_Hurricanes_baseball) has won four national championships since 1982.

Other notable collegiate sports programs in the metropolitan area include the [Florida Atlantic Owls](/Florida_Atlantic_Owls) from [Florida Atlantic University](/Florida_Atlantic_University) in [Boca Raton](/Boca_Raton,_Florida), the [FIU Panthers](/FIU_Panthers) of [Florida International University](/Florida_International_University) in [University Park](/University_Park,_Florida), the [Nova Southeastern Sharks](/Nova_Southeastern_Sharks) from [Nova Southeastern University](/Nova_Southeastern_University) in [Davie](/Davie,_Florida), and the [Barry Buccaneers](/Barry_Buccaneers) of [Barry University](/Barry_University) in [Miami Shores](/Miami_Shores,_Florida).

#### Minor League and Other Sports

The Miami area also hosts several minor league sports teams and other sporting events:

*   The [Miami Marlins](/Miami_Marlins) and [St. Louis Cardinals](/St._Louis_Cardinals) conduct their [spring training](/Spring_training) in [Jupiter](/Jupiter,_Florida) at [Roger Dean Stadium](/Roger_Dean_Stadium).
*   The [Houston Astros](/Houston_Astros) and [Washington Nationals](/Washington_Nationals) hold their [spring training](/Spring_training) in [West Palm Beach](/West_Palm_Beach,_Florida) at [Cacti Park of the Palm Beaches](/Cacti_Park_of_the_Palm_Beaches). [100](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miami_metropolitan_area#cite_note-100), [101](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miami_metropolitan_area#cite_note-101), [102](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miami_metropolitan_area#cite_note-102)
*   [Inter Miami CF](/Inter_Miami_CF) fields a [reserve team](/Inter_Miami_CF_II) that competes in [MLS Next Pro](/MLS_Next_Pro).
*   The [Homestead-Miami Speedway](/Homestead-Miami_Speedway), an oval track, has hosted events for the [NASCAR Cup Series](/NASCAR_Cup_Series) and [IndyCar Series](/IndyCar_Series). Temporary [street circuits](/Street_circuit) at [Museum Park](/Museum_Park_(Miami)) were used for various races, including [CART](/Champ_Car), [IMSA GT](/IMSA_GT), and [American Le Mans Series](/American_Le_Mans_Series) events between 1986 and 1995, as well as a [Formula E race in 2015](/Miami_ePrix). The [Palm Beach International Raceway](/Palm_Beach_International_Raceway) is a smaller road course facility.
*   The [Miami Sharks](/Miami_Sharks_(rugby_union)), a team in [Major League Rugby](/Major_League_Rugby), plays at [AutoNation Sports Field](/AutoNation_Sports_Field) in [Fort Lauderdale](/Fort_Lauderdale,_Florida).

